The paper focuses on information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques to construct evolutionary networks from large text corpora. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, which deals with IR techniques. The paper also involves NLP techniques for entity extraction and connection modeling, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for network construction, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves database techniques for handling large text corpora, which makes cs.DB (Databases) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves social network analysis techniques for modeling connections among entities, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category.
